quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  16,119,"Moreover, your Lord will indeed be forgiving and merciful to those who repent after they having committed evil out of ignorance and reform themselves"
  16,120,"Indeed Abraham was a nation [all by himself], obedient to Allah, a Hanif, and he was not a polytheist"
  16,121,"Grateful [as he was] for His blessings, He chose him and guided him to a straight path"
  16,122,"We gave him good in this world, and in the Hereafter he will indeed be among the Righteous"
  16,123,"Thereafter We revealed to you [saying], ‘Follow the creed of Abraham, a Hanif, who was not a polytheist.’"
  16,124,The Sabbath was only prescribed for those who differed about it. Your Lord will indeed judge between them on the Day of Resurrection concerning that about which they differ
  16,125,"Invite to the way of your Lord with wisdom and good advice and dispute with them in a manner that is best. Indeed your Lord knows best those who stray from His way, and He knows best those who are guided"
  16,126,"Should you retaliate, retaliate with the like of what you have been made to suffer, but if you are patient that is surely better for the steadfast"
  16,127,"So be steadfast, and you cannot be steadfast except with Allah [’s help]. And do not grieve for them, nor be upset by their guile"
  16,128,Indeed Allah is with those who are Godwary and those who are virtuous